1
02:45:40,349 --> 02:45:41,430
[WHISPERING] Hello?

2
02:45:47,109 --> 02:45:48,190
[KNOCKS ECHOING]

3
02:45:56,709 --> 02:45:58,120
[CLEARS THROAT]

4
02:46:00,469 --> 02:46:01,880
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
He's not at home.

5
02:46:02,829 --> 02:46:04,513
Not at home. Ahem.

6
02:46:05,349 --> 02:46:06,430
Good.

7
02:46:08,229 --> 02:46:09,958
Good, good, good.

8
02:47:04,945 --> 02:47:05,960
What's that?

9
02:47:08,829 --> 02:47:10,797
Shush. Shush.

10
02:47:12,109 --> 02:47:13,395
Arkenstone.

11
02:47:14,429 --> 02:47:15,840
Arkenstone.

12
02:47:16,669 --> 02:47:18,717
A large, white jewel.

13
02:47:20,909 --> 02:47:22,274
Very helpful.

14
02:48:00,429 --> 02:48:01,919
[SMAUG EXHALES]

15
02:49:37,789 --> 02:49:39,553
[SNIFFING]

16
02:49:48,251 --> 02:49:49,662
Well...

17
02:49:50,949 --> 02:49:52,235
...thief.

18
02:49:54,229 --> 02:49:57,870
I smell you.

19
02:49:58,229 --> 02:50:01,438
I hear your breath.

20
02:50:03,054 --> 02:50:07,004
I feel your air.

21
02:50:09,844 --> 02:50:12,370
Where are you?

22
02:50:13,843 --> 02:50:14,924
Where are you?

23
02:50:35,035 --> 02:50:38,557
Come now, don't be shy.

24
02:50:39,165 --> 02:50:41,372
Step into the light.

25
02:50:45,940 --> 02:50:46,543
Hmm.

26
02:50:48,378 --> 02:50:51,587
There is something about you.

27
02:50:54,924 --> 02:50:56,806
Something you carry.

28
02:50:57,589 --> 02:51:00,479
Something made of gold.

29
02:51:01,229 --> 02:51:04,153
But far more...

30
02:51:04,389 --> 02:51:06,198
...precious.

31
02:51:06,429 --> 02:51:08,750
VOICE OF THE RING:
<i>Precious! Precious!</i>

32
02:51:11,549 --> 02:51:12,710
There you are...

33
02:51:12,989 --> 02:51:16,592
...Thief in the Shadows.

34
02:51:18,429 --> 02:51:21,035
I did not come to steal from you...

35
02:51:21,499 --> 02:51:24,760
...O Smaug the Unassessably Wealthy.

36
02:51:25,292 --> 02:51:27,690
I merely wanted to gaze upon your magnificence.

37
02:51:28,249 --> 02:51:31,988
To see if you really were
as great as the old tales say.

38
02:51:32,549 --> 02:51:34,278
[WHIMPERS] I did not believe them.

39
02:51:43,109 --> 02:51:47,034
And do you now?!

40
02:51:48,389 --> 02:51:49,629
Truly...

41
02:51:50,949 --> 02:51:53,156
...the tales and songs...

42
02:51:54,711 --> 02:52:00,136
...fall utterly short of your enormity
O Smaug the Stupendous.

43
02:52:00,429 --> 02:52:03,319
Do you think flattery will keep you alive?

44
02:52:03,829 --> 02:52:04,796
No, no.

45
02:52:05,029 --> 02:52:06,519
No, indeed.

46
02:52:08,789 --> 02:52:12,032
You seem familiar with my name...

47
02:52:12,269 --> 02:52:15,159
...but I don't remember smelling
your kind before.

48
02:52:16,698 --> 02:52:20,635
Who are you, and where do you come from...

49
02:52:21,097 --> 02:52:23,190
...may I ask?

50
02:52:32,749 --> 02:52:34,433
I come from under the hill.

51
02:52:35,062 --> 02:52:36,473
Underhill?

52
02:52:39,909 --> 02:52:43,031
BILBO: And under hills and
over hills my path has led.

53
02:52:43,909 --> 02:52:44,751
And... And...

54
02:52:45,509 --> 02:52:47,876
...through the air.
I am he who walks unseen.

55
02:52:48,109 --> 02:52:49,838
Impressive.

56
02:52:50,420 --> 02:52:53,122
What else do you claim to be?

57
02:52:53,490 --> 02:52:54,753
I--I am...

58
02:52:57,109 --> 02:52:58,599
Luck-wearer.

59
02:53:00,223 --> 02:53:01,384
Riddle-maker.

60
02:53:01,781 --> 02:53:03,431
Lovely titles.

61
02:53:04,125 --> 02:53:05,286
<i>Go on.</i>

62
02:53:05,620 --> 02:53:06,701
Barrel-rider.

63
02:53:06,901 --> 02:53:10,303
Barrels? Now that is interesting.

64
02:53:11,924 --> 02:53:15,399
And what about your little Dwarf friends?

65
02:53:16,782 --> 02:53:19,099
Where are they hiding?

66
02:53:20,629 --> 02:53:22,199
Dwarves?

67
02:53:23,029 --> 02:53:24,110
No.

68
02:53:24,991 --> 02:53:27,832
No, no. No Dwarves here.
You've got that all wrong.

69
02:53:28,211 --> 02:53:31,675
Oh, I don't think so, Barrel-rider!

70
02:53:32,447 --> 02:53:35,444
They sent you in here to do their dirty work...

71
02:53:35,725 --> 02:53:38,480
...while they skulk about outside.

72
02:53:39,149 --> 02:53:40,310
Truly...

73
02:53:41,109 --> 02:53:46,032
...you are mistaken, O Smaug,
Chiefest and Greatest of Calamities.

74
02:53:46,274 --> 02:53:49,191
You have nice manners...

75
02:53:49,764 --> 02:53:51,112
...for a thief...

76
02:53:51,470 --> 02:53:52,978
...and a liar!

77
02:53:53,909 --> 02:53:57,311
I know the smell and taste of Dwarf.

78
02:53:58,178 --> 02:54:00,006
<i>No one better!</i>

79
02:54:00,669 --> 02:54:02,080
It is the gold!

80
02:54:02,545 --> 02:54:06,862
They are drawn to treasure
like flies to dead flesh.

81
02:54:10,084 --> 02:54:12,879
Did you think I did not
know this day would come?!

82
02:54:15,181 --> 02:54:20,150
That a pack of canting Dwarves
would come crawling back...

83
02:54:20,709 --> 02:54:22,041
...to the mountain?!

